While the Jawbo may be terrifying to behold, in truth it is quite harmless for trained handlers.\n\nA disproportionately sized mandible makes it impossible for this critter to properly chew its food, necessitating a preference for prey that are small enough to be swallowed whole.\n\nThough much of its DNA suggests that the Jawbo evolved in isolation, it does share a small number of genetic markers with serrasalmids such as the <link=\"PACU\">Pacu</link>. Familial connection, however, does not preclude consideration as a food source.